@database CycleClass
@index "Classes.guide/Main"

@Node Main "RxMUI - Cycle Class"


Cycle class    @{"Index" link "Classes.guide/Main"} @{"Super" link "GroupClass.guide/Main"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The Cycle class is used to create cycle gadgets.

  You must pass in Entries a string made of the entries of the
  cycle gadgets separated with | .

  See @{"MakeObj()" LINK "Functions.guide/MakeObj"}.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Active@{fg text}
  M ISGN
  G2N A number or one of:
     o Next
     o Prev

  @{fg shine}ActiveEntry@{fg text}
  S ISGN
  It is one of the entries specified in Entries. The comparation
  is no-case. If you set it to a string that doesn't match any
  entry, just nothing happens.

  @{fg shine}Entries@{fg text}
  S I IND

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  None defined

@EndNode
